  "local_port": 44062,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you bake frozen hash browns?",
  "response": "Baking frozen hash browns is a straightforward process. Here's a simple method to achieve crispy and delicious hash browns:\n\n### Ingredients:\n- Frozen hash browns (shredded or patties)\n- Cooking spray or vegetable oil\n- Salt and pepper (optional)\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Preheat the Oven**: \n   - Preheat your oven to 425\u00b0F (220\u00b0C).\n\n2. **Prepare the Baking Sheet**:\n   - Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or aluminum foil for easy cleanup.\n   - Spray the sheet lightly with cooking spray or brush it with a thin layer of vegetable oil to prevent sticking.\n\n3. **Arrange Hash Browns**:\n   - Spread the frozen hash browns evenly across the prepared baking sheet. If you're using patties, place them in a single layer without overlapping.\n   - For shredded hash browns, spread them out flat to ensure even cooking.\n\n4. **Spray or Drizzle with Oil**:\n   - Lightly spray the tops of the hash browns with cooking spray or drizzle with a small amount of vegetable oil. This will help them crisp up nicely.\n\n5. **Season** (Optional):\n   - Add salt, pepper, or any other seasonings to taste.\n\n6. **Bake**:\n   - Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven.\n   - Bake for about 15 minutes, then remove the sheet and flip the hash browns or stir them gently if using shredded ones.\n   - Return them to the oven and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the hash browns are golden brown and crispy.\n\n7. **Check for Doneness**:\n   - The exact time may vary based on your oven and the type of hash browns, so keep an eye on them towards the end to ensure they don't overcook.\n\n8. **Serve**:\n   - Once done, remove the hash browns from the oven and let them sit for a minute or two before serving.\n\nEnjoy your crispy baked hash browns! Feel free to customize them by adding cheese, herbs, or other toppings during the last few minutes of baking.",
